article:
This is a 'List of San Francisco Designated Landmarks'. In 1967, the City of San
Francisco, in the U.S. state of California adopted Article 10 of the Planning
Code providing the city with the authority to designate and protect landmarks
from inappropriate alterations. In total, the city has designated 261 structures
or other properties as San Francisco Designated Landmarks. Many of the
properties have also received recognition at the federal level by inclusion on
the National Register of Historic Places or by designation as National Historic
Landmarks.
